author: AddictedToStyrene
title: Too simple
review: Even for Jack Stone, this was a very simple set. It's just a couple of wing/click hinges, a tail and a propellor. It was a good way of getting those parts cheap if you needed them. I did the opposite to Spartacus: I bought the set for the Jack Stone figure to fly in the 3451 Sopwith Camel!
